cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.CV, cs.BIO, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for analyzing gait patterns in clinical biomechanics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of Layer-Wise Relevance Propagation (LRP) technique, which falls under the category of interpretability and explainability of machine learning models, making cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) another likely category. The paper also involves computer vision techniques for analyzing gait patterns, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method in medical diagnoses, which falls under the category of cs.BIO (Computational Biology) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
